article.headline: Radford edges Liberty 87-83
article.story: LYNCHBERG, Va. -- Javonte Greene scored 25 points and grabbed 12 rebounds as Radford held on for an 87-83 victory over Liberty on Saturday. Ya Ya Anderson had 19 points for the Highlanders (20-11, 10-6 Big South). Rashun Davis came off the bench to score 18 points and R.J. Price added 10. Radford went 20-11 early in the second period to lead 54-51 before the Flames responded with a 13-2 run anchored by three John-Caleb Sanders 3-pointers to go back up 64-56 with 10:40 remaining. Trailing by nine with 5:17 to play, Anderson hit a pair of 3-pointers -- and Price added another -- to help the Highlanders build a 79-75 lead. They held on for the win, despite a Davon Marshall 3 in the final seconds that brought the Flames within two. Antwan Burrus led the Flames (11-20, 5-11) with 19 points and eight rebounds.
